{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4d93ce8d-abb6-4615-8f32-f1da26b59425","content":"You can filter by class name using the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\"\n```\n\nOr more precisely by class:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"ClassName=ReportExporterTests\"\n```\n\nIf it's in a namespace (e.g., `MyApp.Tests.ReportExporterTests`), you can use the fully qualified name:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\"\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so it matches any test whose fully qualified name includes `ReportExporterTests`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2d3fd3cb-2456-436d-b997-575a72122a2a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. Let me first look at the test files to understand the structure.","outputTokens":210,"requestId":"4C60:21DE79:BB49C3:E8ED69:6A0130AB"},"id":"76a547cb-c4fb-493d-b7a2-f8f4929543f3","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:28:16.787Z","parentId":"c5e6becf-873c-4378-8898-30a844435bc9"}
